FBIS4-51895 "dreas086_l_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-086 Daily Report 29 Apr 1994 Philippines CPP Expells Two More Top Anti-Sison Leaders CPP Expells Two More Top Anti-Sison Leaders BK0405023994 Manila PHILIPPINE DAILY INQUIRER in English 29 Apr 94 p 7 BK0405023994 Manila PHILIPPINE DAILY INQUIRER English BFN [Text] Two more top communist leaders in Mindanao were expelled from the underground movement for their refusal to recognize Jose Maria Sison as the chair of the Communist Party of the Philippines (CPP), reports reaching Camp Aguinaldo said yesterday. Col. Angelo Reyes, commanding officer of the Civil Relations Service (CRS) of the Armed Forces of the Philippines, said the CPP "faces more serious crises" due to the worsening rift within the movement." Reyes identified those expelled as Timoteo Pupa, Central Mindanao Regional Committee (CMRC) secretary and Ike de los Reyes, Pupa's deputy.
